1. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper heavily relies on combinatorial methods and graph theory to study the Weak Symmetry Breaking task, and introduces a new class of graphs called flip graphs. 
2. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper deals with the complexity of solving the Weak Symmetry Breaking task, which is a fundamental problem in game theory. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper presents an explicitly constructed 3-round IIS protocol for solving the Weak Symmetry Breaking task, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper analyzes the iterated immediate snapshot (IIS) complexity of the Weak Symmetry Breaking task, which is a measure of computational complexity. 
5. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The Weak Symmetry Breaking task is a problem that arises in the context of distributed computing and communication networks, which falls under the purview of social and information networks.
